# npm    : `hunkdiff` (provides two bin aliases — `hunk` for the
#          short form and `hunkdiff` matching the npm package name;
#          both bin entries point to ./bin/hunk.cjs which is a small
#          Node shim that finds and exec's the platform-specific
#          Bun-compiled binary from npm's `@hunkdiff/bin-darwin-arm64
#          / bin-linux-x64 / bin-windows-x64` sibling packages — the
#          actual TypeScript app is compiled with Bun's single-binary
#          output for fast startup)
#
# Source-direct completion: every subcommand + flag below is verbatim
# from src/core/cli.ts on the modem-dev/hunk tip — the `renderCliHelp`
# function returns the help text that this completion mirrors, and
# per-subcommand flag tables come from the same file's command-
# specific `renderHelp*` functions.  Global review options (--mode,
# --watch, --agent-context, --pager, --line-numbers, --wrap, --hunk-
# headers, --agent-notes, --theme) apply to all subcommands that
# render diffs (diff / show / patch / pager / difftool / stash show).
#
# Direct deps from package.json (selected):
#   diff                  ^8.0.3   ← canonical JS text-diff library
#                                     (this axis) — by Kevin Decker
#                                     (kpdecker/jsdiff); pure-JS
#                                     implementation of Myers diff
#                                     with the Hunt-McIlroy and
#                                     Underwood variants, plus
#                                     granularity selectors for char
#                                     / word / line / sentence / CSS /
#                                     JSON / array diffing.  Each
#                                     granularity exposes a separate
#                                     `Diff.diffChars` / `diffWords` /
#                                     `diffLines` / `diffSentences` /
#                                     `diffCss` / `diffJson` /
#                                     `diffArrays` entry point that
#                                     returns an array of `Change`
#                                     objects (`{ added, removed,
#                                     value, count }`).  THE de-facto-
#                                     standard JS embedded diff
#                                     library — used by Mocha (test
#                                     diff output), Jest (snapshot
#                                     diffs), every JS code-review
#                                     tool, Prettier (printing the
#                                     diff between formatted and
#                                     unformatted output), VS Code's
#                                     extension API diff renderer,
#                                     babel-plugin-fixture-test-diff,
#                                     and dozens of unified-diff
#                                     formatting tools.  Sister
#                                     project to the older `diff-
#                                     match-patch` by Neil Fraser (the
#                                     Google library that `sergi/go-
#                                     diff` is a port of — covered in
#                                     the previous round's
#                                     _identify_license completion);
#                                     `jsdiff` diverged from that
#                                     codebase as a clean-room JS
#                                     implementation with a more
#                                     ergonomic API surface, while
#                                     `diff-match-patch` continues to
#                                     exist as `google/diff-match-
#                                     patch` for cross-language
#                                     compatibility with Java / Python
#                                     / Lua / Objective-C / C# / Dart
#                                     ports.  Hunk uses `diff` inside
#                                     src/core/diffFile.ts to compute
#                                     the per-hunk line-level diff
#                                     between the working-tree state
#                                     and the indexed/staged state
#                                     when git is unavailable to
#                                     produce the diff (e.g. when
#                                     comparing two arbitrary files
#                                     via `hunk diff before.ts
#                                     after.ts`), and for the patch-
#                                     parsing path when input comes
#                                     from `hunk patch -` (stdin).
#                                     For the more common git-backed
#                                     case, hunk shells out to `git
#                                     diff` / `git show` to get the
#                                     server-computed diff bytes and
#                                     parses them with @pierre/diffs
#                                     (the higher-level diff-parser
#                                     companion library mentioned in
#                                     the README).
#   @pierre/diffs                   (Pierre diffs — higher-level diff
#                                     parser; eats git-style unified
#                                     diff bytes and emits structured
#                                     hunk objects for the renderer)
#   @opentui/core + @opentui/react  (OpenTUI — the React-based
#                                     terminal UI framework by
#                                     anomalyco that Hunk renders
#                                     against; alternative to ratatui-
#                                     for-Node / blessed / Ink)
#   bun + @types/bun                (Bun runtime — Hunk is shipped
#                                     as a Bun-compiled single binary
#                                     for fast startup; the Node shim
#                                     in bin/hunk.cjs only exists for
#                                     npm-install convenience and
#                                     immediately exec's the Bun
#                                     binary on first run)
#   simple-git + @octokit/* + chalk + zod + yaml
#
# Hunk is "git difftool, but built for the AI-agent-authoring era" —
# instead of looking at a unified diff in less + delta + bat, you
# launch `hunk diff` and review the changeset in a multi-file sidebar
# TUI with split / stack / auto layouts, optional inline agent notes
# explaining the rationale behind each change (via JSON sidecar files
# the agent writes), and watch mode that auto-reloads as the agent
# continues making changes in another terminal.  The `hunk session`
# subcommand exposes a session-broker API over a Unix domain socket so
# the agent can query "what is the user looking at right now? did they
# accept hunk 3? did they reject hunk 7?" without scraping stdout.
# Git integration is the default, but Jujutsu (jj) is auto-detected
# and `[revset]` arguments are interpreted as jj revsets in a jj
# workspace.  `hunk skill path` prints the bundled `SKILL.md` file
# that Claude Code / Codex CLI / Cursor can load to learn how to
# coordinate with a running Hunk session.
#
